        super(MLP_net, self).__init__()
        self.hidden1 = nn.Linear(n_feature, 60)
        self.hidden2 = nn.Linear(60, 120)
        self.result = nn.Linear(120, 10)


    def forward(self, x):
        hidd1 = self.hidden1(x)
        hidd2 = self.hidden2(hidd1)
        y = self.result(hidd2)
        return y

# Rule,sigmoid
## nn.Module
class MLP_net(nn.Module):
    # init
    def __init__(self, n_feature):
        super(MLP_net, self).__init__()
        self.hidden1 = nn.Linear(n_feature, 60)
        self.hidden2 = nn.Linear(60, 120)
        self.result = nn.Linear(120, 10)

    # forward
    def forward(self, x):
        hidd1 = nn.functional.relu(self.hidden1(x))
        hidd2 = nn.functional.relu(self.hidden2(hidd1))
        y = torch.sigmoid(self.result(hidd2))
        return y
# 
net = MLP_net(num_inputs)
print(net)     # [784, 60, 120, 10]

MLP_net(
  (hidden1): Linear(in_features=784, out_features=60, bias=True)
  (hidden2): Linear(in_features=60, out_features=120, bias=True)
  (result): Linear(in_features=120, out_features=10, bias=True)
)
In [7]:
# Rule,sigmoid
## nn.Module
class MLP_net(nn.Module):
    # init
    def __init__(self, n_feature):
        super(MLP_net, self).__init__()
        self.hidden1 = nn.Linear(n_feature, 60)
        self.hidden2 = nn.Linear(60, 120)
        self.result = nn.Linear(120, 10)

    # forward
    def forward(self, x):
        hidd1= nn.functional.dropout(nn.functional.relu(self.hidden1(x)),p=0.5)
        hidd2 = nn.functional.dropout(nn.functional.relu(self.hidden2(hidd1)),p=0.5)
        y = torch.sigmoid(self.result(hidd2))
        return y
# 
net = MLP_net(num_inputs)
print(net)     # [784, 60, 120, 10]

MLP_net(
  (hidden1): Linear(in_features=784, out_features=60, bias=True)
  (hidden2): Linear(in_features=60, out_features=120, bias=True)
  (result): Linear(in_features=120, out_features=10, bias=True)
)

num_epoch = 3
## 
for epoch in range(num_epoch):
    train_l_sum,train_acc_sum = 0.0,0.0
    for x, y in train:
        # print(type(x.view(-1,784).shape))
        y_pre = net(x.view(-1, 784))
        # print(y_pre)
        l = loss(y_pre, y).sum()
        # print(l)

        optimizer.zero_grad()
        l.backward()
        optimizer.step()

        train_l_sum += l.item()
        train_acc_sum += (y_pre.argmax(dim=1) ==y).sum().item()
        sum = y.shape[0]
#     print(train_l_sum/len(train))
    print('epoch:'+ str(epoch + 1), 'loss:'+str(train_l_sum/len(train)))

# dropout,drop_p(),keep_p
def dropout(data, drop_p):
    data = data.float()
    # 
    assert 0 <= drop_p <= 1
    # 
    keep_p = 1 - drop_p
    # 
    if keep_p == 0:
        return torch.zeros_like(data)
    # keep_pkeep_p
    mask = (torch.randn(data.shape) < keep_p).float()
    
    return mask * data / keep_p
